"{\"uid\": \"www.theguardian.com.-commentisfree-2016-jul-03-marine-le-pen-brexit-france-victor-hugo-humanity-Part2\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Europe, allow me to give you this name.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 39, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You exist, therefore it exists.\", \"from\": 40, \"to\": 71, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You confirm it by the union from which unity is taking shape.\", \"from\": 72, \"to\": 133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are the beginning of a great future.\\\"\", \"from\": 134, \"to\": 175, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, most of us, like Hugo, are heirs to the idea of nation states, trying to reconcile our love for our countries with a desire to be part of a bigger ensemble - a strong, generous and rich political and economic European Union.\", \"from\": 177, \"to\": 408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it is difficult.\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are torn, unsure.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, what is it to be European?\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Hugo, the answer is simple.\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To be and feel European is not to renounce one's identity; it is, on the contrary, to add an extra layer to it and make it richer.\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have written with a profound love for my own country, but without being engrossed by France more than by any other nation.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As I advance in life, I grow more simple, and I become more and more patriotic for humanity.\\\"\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Europe, a patriotism for humanity - what a beautiful and appropriate definition in our troubled times.\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whichever direction Britain finally chooses to take, leaving the EU, voting again or ignoring the referendum's results, there is still hope that Hugo's dream might one day be achieved - if not by our generation, then by the next one, or the one after.\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": []}]}"